  "title": "Rifle ShootReload MocapAnimPack",
  "description": "This is a realistic animation, that was shot using Mocap technology, designed for gamedev.",
  "longDescription": "<p>VIDEO: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v&#61;xQHSpH-g_pQ\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v&#61;xQHSpH-g_pQ</a></p><p>Video How To retarget Animation Packs from UE4 to UE5: <a href=\"https://youtu.be/jpVjnnVQ6dA\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://youtu.be/jpVjnnVQ6dA</a></p><p><br /></p><p>This pack contains two parts:</p><p>1) ShootingSet</p><p>2) ReloadingSet</p><p>Each of these parts uses four different rifles in four different poses. These are the most used game guns (Winchester, Automatic, ShotGun and DoubleBarrel)</p>",
  "technicalDetails": "<p>Reload animations are made so, that the moment of bullet supply can be easily cut off as a separate animation. This allows to change the number of rifle bullet loads.Â </p><p>The shots and reloads are performed from four positions:</p><p>- Rifle01_Stand_Style</p><p>- Rifle02_Stand_Style</p><p>- Rifle03_Stand_Style</p><p>- Rifle_Crouch_Style</p><p><br /></p><p>Overall the pack contains 42 animations (fbx format).</p><p><br /></p><p>Update 1.1. This update includes the following changes:</p><ul><li>animated virtual bones;</li><li>added Source folder (contains all animations in FBX format, they can be integrated into any version of Unreal Engine).</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Rigged to Epic skeleton: Yes</p><p>IK bones are included: Yes</p><p>Animation types: Root Motion and In-place</p><p><br /></p><p>Supported Development Platforms:</p><p>Windows: Yes</p><p>Mac: Yes</p>",
